age / Dirty Monkey\n |DirectedBy='''Room Rage:''' Becky Bristow<br />'''Dirty Monkey:''' Tamara Varga\n |WrittenBy='''Room Rage:''' Andrew Brenner<br />'''Dirty Monkey:''' Brian Wood\n |OriginalAirDate={{start date|2002|6|23}}\n |ShortSummary= '''Room Rage:''' Mrs Cramp demands that every room in the house is kept clean.\n----\n'''Dirty Monkey:''' Mrs Cramp wins a competition for a free beauty makeover for the whole family.\n |LineColor=7D4185\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=16\n |EpisodeNumber2=16\n |Title=Mr. Winkle's Monkey / Wicked Wendy\n |DirectedBy='''Mr. Winkle's Monkey''' & '''Wicked Wendy'''<br />Becky Bristow\n |WrittenBy='''Mr. Winkle's Monkey:''' Andrew Brenner<br />'''Wicked Wendy:''' Ken Koonce and Gene Braunstein\n |OriginalAirDate={{start date|2002|6|30}}\n |ShortSummary= '''Mr. Winkle's Monkey:''' On their annual class trip to the Haz Chem Soap Factory, Lucien and Mari discover a mangy monkey on the premises.\n----\n'''Wicked Wendy:''' A silent clown shows up at the Cramps' front door, advertising the opening of a new trampoline amusement park.\n |LineColor=7D4185\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=17\n |EpisodeNumber2=17\n |Title=Haircut Horrors / Nostalgia Nasty\n |DirectedBy='''Haircut Horrors''' & '''Nostalgia Nasty'''<br />Becky Bristow\n |WrittenBy='''Haircut Horrors:''' Sean Veder<br />'''Nostalgia Nasty:''' Ben Joseph\n |OriginalAirDate={{start date|2002|7|7}}\n |ShortSummary= '''Haircut Horrors:''' Mrs. Cramp decides that the boys need an urgent haircut but finds out that the barber is too dirty to cut the boys' hair.\n----\n'''Nostalgia Nasty:''' When Wayne discovers an old-fashioned cast-iron laundry mangle, it sends Mr. and Mrs. Cramp into a full-blown nostalgia mania.\n |LineColor=7D4185\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=18\n |EpisodeNumber2=18\n |Title=No Means Yes / Spy's Pies\n |DirectedBy='''No Means Yes''' & '''Spy's Pies'''<br />Becky Bristow\n |WrittenBy='''No Means Yes:''' Dennis Haley and Marcey Brown<br />'''Spy's Pies:''' David Polsky\n |OriginalAirDate={{start date|2002|7|14}}\n |ShortSummary= '''No Means Yes:''' Lucien reluctantly agrees to stand in for Mari at parent-teacher night.\n----\n'''Spy's Pies:''' A new neighbor is determined to find out Mrs. Cramp's secret for cleaning.\n |LineColor=7D4185\n}}\n}}\n\n===Season 2 (2003)===\n{{Episode table| background=#A11F78|overall=5|season=5|title=20|director=17|writer=17|airdate=12|episodes=\n\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=19\n |EpisodeNumber2=1\n |Title=Home on the Range / Holesome\n |DirectedBy='''Home on the Range''' & '''Holesome'''<br />Becky Bristow\n |WrittenBy='''Home on the Range:''' Richard Liebmann-Smith<br />'''Holesome:''' [[Andrew Brenner (writer)|Andrew Brenner]]\n |OriginalAirDate={{start date|2003|1|29}}\n |ShortSummary=\n |LineColor=A11F78\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=20\n |EpisodeNumber2=2\n |Title=Picket, Picket / Sick Daze\n |DirectedBy='''Picket, Picket:''' TBA<br />'''Sick Daze:''' Becky Bristow\n |WrittenBy='''Picket, Picket:''' Brian Wood<br />'''Sick Daze:''' Sean Veder\n |OriginalAirDate={{start date|2003|2|12}}\n |ShortSummary=\n |LineColor=A11F78\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=21\n |EpisodeNumber2=3\n |Title=Big Baby / Ad Bad\n |DirectedBy='''Big Baby''' & '''Ad Bad'''<br />Becky Bristow\n |WrittenBy='''Big Baby:''' Randolph Heard<br />'''Ad Bad:''' Ken Koonce and Gene Braunstein\n |OriginalAirDate={{start date|2003|2|19}}\n |ShortSummary=\n |LineColor=A11F78\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=22\n |EpisodeNumber2=4\n |Title=Workout / 6th Senselessness\n |DirectedBy='''Workout''' & '''6th Senselessness'''<br />Becky Bristow\n |WrittenBy='''Workout''' & '''6th Senselessness'''<br />Andrew Brenner\n |OriginalAirDate={{start date|2003|2|26}}\n |ShortSummary=\n |LineColor=A11F78\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=23\n |EpisodeNumber2=5\n |Title=Hotel Hysteria / Alien Glow\n |DirectedBy='''Hotel Hysteria:''' Becky Bristow<br />'''Alien Glow:''' Tamara Varga\n |WrittenBy='''Hotel Hys